The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 26 November is 110,423 (12,726.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 21 November, there were 5,370 new confirmed cases (618.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 November, there were 4,746 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 13% (624 extra cases).
